  </study_design_info>
  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Mean change in vertigo intensity.</measure>
    <time_frame>At 2 hours after intervention.</time_frame>
    <description>The primary efficacy outcome was the mean change in the vertigo intensity score between pre- and post-intervention at 2 hours after administration of study medications.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>Efficacy and Safety outcome measures (nausea change-second dose-adverse events).</measure>
    <time_frame>At 2-8 hours after intervention.</time_frame>
    <description>Secondary outcomes included, mean change in nausea VAS score, need for second dose of study medications, and the rate of drug-related adverse events for the subjects in each study group after intervention.</description>
  </secondary_outcome>
